# Project Structure

## Directory Layout

```
project-root/
├── .cursorrules/          # Cursor rules and guidelines
├── src/                   # Source code
│   ├── components/        # Reusable UI components
│   ├── pages/             # Page components
│   ├── features/          # Feature modules
│   ├── hooks/             # Custom React hooks
│   ├── services/          # API services and business logic
│   ├── utils/             # Utility functions
│   ├── types/             # TypeScript type definitions
│   ├── constants/         # Application constants
│   ├── styles/            # Global styles and themes
│   └── assets/            # Static assets (images, fonts)
├── tests/                 # Test utilities and setup
├── docs/                  # Documentation
├── public/                # Public static files
├── config/                # Configuration files
└── scripts/               # Build and utility scripts
```

## Feature-Based Organization

For larger projects, organize by features:

```
src/
├── features/
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   ├── hooks/
│   │   ├── services/
│   │   ├── types/
│   │   └── index.ts
│   ├── dashboard/
│   │   ├── components/
│   │   ├── hooks/
│   │   └── index.ts
│   └── profile/
│       ├── components/
│       └── index.ts
├── shared/                # Shared across features
│   ├── components/
│   ├── hooks/
│   └── utils/
└── app/                   # App-level configuration
```

## File Organization Principles

### Co-location
Keep related files together:
```
components/
└── Button/
    ├── Button.tsx
    ├── Button.test.tsx
    ├── Button.stories.tsx
    └── index.ts
```

### Separation of Concerns
- **Components** - UI presentation
- **Hooks** - Reusable logic
- **Services** - API and business logic
- **Utils** - Pure utility functions
- **Types** - Type definitions

## Import Paths

### Use Absolute Imports
```typescript
// ✅ Good: Absolute imports with alias
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';
import { useAuth } from '@/hooks/useAuth';
import { UserService } from '@/services/UserService';

// ❌ Bad: Relative imports
import { Button } from '../../../components/Button';
```

### Path Aliases Configuration
```json
// tsconfig.json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["src/*"],
      "@/components/*": ["src/components/*"],
      "@/hooks/*": ["src/hooks/*"],
      "@/services/*": ["src/services/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Consistent structure** - Follow the same pattern throughout
2. **Feature-based when scaling** - Organize by feature for large projects
3. **Co-locate related files** - Keep tests and stories with components
4. **Use barrel exports** - Simplify imports with index.ts files
5. **Clear separation** - Separate concerns (UI, logic, data)
6. **Document structure** - Keep README files in key directories
